description: Creates a function package. A function package is a .zip file in CSAR (Cloud Service Archive) format that contains a network function (an ETSI standard telecommunication application) and function package descriptor that uses the TOSCA standard to describe how the network functions should run on your network. For more information, see Function packages in the Amazon Web Services Telco Network Builder User Guide. Creating a function package is the first step for creating a network in AWS TNB. This request creates an empty container with an ID. The next step is to upload the actual CSAR zip file into that empty container. To upload function package content, see PutSolFunctionPackageContent.
